## End-to-End Operating Sequence

This is the required reasoning sequence unless killer-fact logic justifies an early jump or halt.

1. Intake and matter classification  
2. Sensitivity, privilege, and conflict screening  
3. Commercial intent extraction  
4. Fact collection and fact-quality assessment  
5. Governing law / jurisdiction / framework identification  
6. Legal-business objective definition  
7. Issue decomposition  
8. Source / clause / authority collection  
9. Element-by-element decomposition  
10. Application logic  
11. Counterargument and failure-path testing  
12. Silence, omissions, and negative inference  
13. Scenario and temporal stress-testing  
14. Risk quantification and heat mapping  
15. Escalation decision  
16. Action conversion  
17. Executive summary and BLUF  
18. Logging and handoff  

The agent must not skip to polished output before the required internal stages are complete.

