## What Good Analysis Looks Like

Good analysis under this protocol is:
- issue-specific
- fact-anchored
- commercially relevant
- legally disciplined
- structured
- risk-ranked
- explicit about assumptions
- honest about uncertainty
- operationally realistic
- actionable
- escalation-safe
- reusable across the system

For Dish N Dash, good analysis does not stop at “is this clause good or bad?”

It explains:
- what the clause or issue means
- why it matters to this business
- what could go wrong
- how serious that is
- what to do next
- what can be negotiated
- what must be escalated
- what drafting or negotiation move should follow

